 1357da-ef8f-4724-af97-7422464525a0777f1e0b-2752-4629-8899-0740ca07efe2.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nWhat does it mean to be&nbs
 p\;an "other"? How can writing shift the boundaries between insider and ou
 tsider for both author and audience? All are welcome to join the ACC in di
 scussing these questions over dinner through Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay col
 lection&nbsp\; To Save and&nbsp\;to Destroy: Writing as an Other . Origina
 lly delivered as the Norton Lecture series at Harvard in 2023-24\, the six
  chapters span Nguyen's reflections on war\, solidarity\, and power\, draw
 ing from sources ranging from classics of American literature to Nguyen's 
 own lived experience as a refugee. Digital copies of the eBook are&nbsp\; 
 freely available to access through IU Libraries \, so all attendees are we
 lcome to read ahead! Pizza will be served at each meeting. &nbsp\; For mor
 e information\, please reach out to ACC volunteer and book club moderator 
 Cheryl Nong\, PhD student in social psychology\, at&nbsp\; acc@iu.edu . Th
 e next book club meeting is on March 26\, 2026.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; All In
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
