DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nThis film event is part of&
 nbsp\;First&nbsp\;Thursdays.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; About the film: When the massi
 ve Thirty Meter Telescope is proposed to be built on Mauna Kea\, an uprisi
 ng of&nbsp\; kiaʻi &nbsp\;(protectors) in Hawaiʻi and around the world d
 edicate their lives to protecting the sacred mountain from destruction. Th
 rough the lens of mothers and daughters in three Native Hawaiian families\
 ,&nbsp\; Standing Above the Clouds &nbsp\;explores intergenerational heali
 ng and the impacts of safeguarding cultural traditions.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; All
  Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, and&nbsp\;educational\,
  cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other m
 embers of the Indiana University community.
LOCATION:Indiana University Cinema
