BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Paul Lucas Graduate History Conference
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T120000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T210000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11981599
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: History Graduate Student Association\n\nThe History
  Graduate Student Association (HGSA) at Indiana University is organizing t
 he annual Paul Lucas Graduate History Conference on Friday and Saturday\, 
 April 3 and April 4\, 2026. This interdisciplinary conference is inspired 
 by the manifold questions raised by the notion of &ldquo\;crisis.&rdquo\; 
 We welcome submissions for individual papers from graduate students of all
  disciplines\, including\, but not limited to\, History\, Anthropology\, P
 olitical Science\, Sociology\, Geography\, Art History &amp\; Literature\,
  Religious Studies\, Area Studies\, Cultural Studies\, Gender Studies\, an
 d Queer Studies. Proposals may include any temporal\, thematic\, and geogr
 aphic approaches to historical inquiry.
LOCATION:IMU Dogwood Room April 3rd & IMU Walnut Room April 4th
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11981599
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Indiana University Traditional Powwow
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T210000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12311686
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/f0
 e8a699-9c82-4e0b-8974-61a40faf6344f7233f3c-91b7-4d84-82c5-cfba95b28c9e.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: First Nations Educational and Cultural Center\n\n13
 th Annual Powwow Saturday\, April 4\, 2026 12&ndash\;5 p.m. Wilkinson Hall
  The Indiana University annual Traditional Powwow attracts hundreds of vis
 itors each year and boasts a line-up of nationally known dancers and singe
 rs\, along with traditional foods\, crafts\, and dance clothing. Performer
 s of all ages participate\, carrying on the traditions of their people as 
 they represent them through their feathers and beadwork\, their dance clot
 hes\, the songs they sing\, and the styles in which they dance. The powwow
  is an important time when generations come together to share in dance and
  song\, and to celebrate the diversity of contemporary Native American tri
 bal identity. In addition to the social dancing at IU&rsquo\;s Traditional
  Powwow\, vendors offer handcrafted items such as silver and turquoise jew
 elry\, blankets\, artwork\, beaded purses\, and other accessories.&nbsp\;
LOCATION:Wilkinson Hall
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12311686
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
