DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nJoin students from Purdue U
 niversity\, the University of Minnesota\, the University of Illinois Urban
 a-Champaign\, and the University of Illinois Chicago for a thought-provoki
 ng virtual discussion of&nbsp\; Fetishized &nbsp\;by Kaila Yu. The author 
 will join us for a Q&amp\;A to share insights about her writing and the cu
 ltural conversations that inspired the book. &nbsp\; &nbsp\; In&nbsp\; Fet
 ishized \, Kaila Yu explores the intersections of race\, gender\, and medi
 a representation through deeply personal reflections on being an Asian Ame
 rican woman in today&rsquo\;s world.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;A&nbsp\; New York Times 
 &nbsp\;review praised Yu&rsquo\;s writing as &ldquo\;searingly honest and 
 culturally resonant\,&rdquo\; noting that her book &ldquo\;pushes readers 
 to confront uncomfortable truths about the persistence of fetishization an
 d the power of self-narration.&rdquo\;&nbsp\; To access the e-book version
  of&nbsp\; Fetishized \, please visit &nbsp\;IUCAT&nbsp\; https://iucat.iu
 .edu/i
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12327818
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
