 apter of Sigma Lambda Beta International Fraternity Inc. is planning a r e
 productive rights expo \, a small-scale\, interactive event designed to ed
 ucate and engage the university community on critical issues affecting wom
 en&rsquo\;s rights\, gender equity\, and reproductive choice. The event wi
 ll feature themed tables staffed by volunteers or organizational represent
 atives\, where attendees can explore topics\, ask questions\, and particip
 ate in hands-on activities. Think of it as a college-style fair focused on
  women&rsquo\;s issues \, with each table serving as a mini-workshop or in
 formation hub. It will not be a protest nor a political demonstration\, ra
 ther it will be an informational event. There will also be a philanthropic
  element\, as one of the tables will be constructing care packages (contai
 ning&nbsp\; pads\, soap\, toothbrush/toothpaste\, socks\, gloves\,&nbsp\;p
 rotein bars\, water\, nuts\, trail mix\, etc.) which will be donated to Mi
