BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Recovery Ally Training
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T193000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12164957
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/2f
 3fff29-c267-4789-92bd-eb4ee3f840d24fcb9b09-c7e7-495c-8181-ca634fef4015.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Collegiate Recovery Community\n\nRecovery Ally Trai
 ning is an interactive educational workshop designed to increase awareness
 \, reduce stigma\, and build practical skills to support individuals in re
 covery from substance use disorders. Participants will learn about recover
 y pathways\, common challenges faced by people in recovery\, and how langu
 age\, policies\, and everyday interactions can either support or hinder re
 covery efforts. This training emphasizes empathy\, inclusivity\, and actio
 nable strategies\, empowering participants to serve as visible\, informed 
 allies within their communities\, workplaces\, or campuses. By the end of 
 the training\, attendees will have a stronger understanding of recovery-or
 iented practices and how to create safer\, more supportive environments fo
 r people in recovery.
LOCATION:Wellness House 115
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12164957
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:ACC Book Club features “To Save and Destroy” by Viet Nguyen
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T210000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T220000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11950465
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/80
 1357da-ef8f-4724-af97-7422464525a0777f1e0b-2752-4629-8899-0740ca07efe2.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nThis is our last book discu
 ssion meeting. What does it mean to be&nbsp\;an "other"? How can writing s
 hift the boundaries between insider and outsider for both author and audie
 nce? All are welcome to join the ACC in discussing these questions over pi
 zza. We will discuss the last two essays of Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay coll
 ection&nbsp\; To Save and to Destroy: Writing as an Other . Digital copies
  of the eBook are&nbsp\; freely available to access through IU Libraries &
 nbsp\; &nbsp\; For more information\, please reach out to ACC volunteer an
 d book club moderator Cheryl Nong\, PhD student in social psychology\, at&
 nbsp\; acc@iu.edu .&nbsp\;&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; All Indiana Univ
 ersity events\, groups\, activities\, and&nbsp\;educational\, cultural\, a
 nd historical observances welcome all IU students and other members of the
  Indiana University community.
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11950465
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
