BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Denim Day
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T180000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12234577
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/87
 c9fa44-e97c-423d-8c21-131475e3fce9b92f37a4-58af-45f8-928b-549bcec94d3e.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Office for Sexual Violence Prevention and Victim Ad
 vocacy\n\nDenim Day is recognized on the last Wednesday in April in honor 
 of Sexual Assault Awareness Month. The campaign began after a ruling by th
 e Italian Supreme Court to overturn a rape conviction because the justices
  felt that since the victim was wearing tight jeans she must have helped t
 he person who raped her remove them\, thereby implying consent. Following 
 the reversal\, the women in the Italian Parliament came to work wearing je
 ans in solidarity with the victim. Join the Office for Sexual Violence Pre
 vention and Victim Advocacy and sexual assault survivors worldwide in wear
 ing jeans and learning about more you can do to provide a safe and support
 ive environment.&nbsp\;
LOCATION:10th St and Fee at Arboretum - Table 1
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12234577
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
