DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Student Advisory Board of the Department of Compara
 tive Literature\n\nIt&rsquo\;s About Time! &nbsp\;--&nbsp\;It is always ti
 mely to talk about time\, but\, perhaps now more than ever\, time is of th
 e essence. So\, what are we waiting for? The central theme of this confere
 nce is temporality &ndash\; which may be broadly defined as the study of t
 ime and experiences related to time. This includes individual and collecti
 ve perceptions of the flow of time\; human and/or non-human experiences of
  time\; changes\, or perceived changes in the flow of time and their effec
 ts on the pace and movement of life\, work\, and art.
LOCATION:IMU Oak Room
